cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about image super-resolution, which is a computer vision task, so it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also discusses approaches for training deep neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a data synthesis method, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of MixUp, a learning principle, could also suggest that the paper belongs to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the NTIRE2019 Real SR Challenge, which is a competition related to multimedia, so the paper could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
